Docker Volumes : It allows you to persist the data generate and used by docker container . This stored the data outside
                 the file system making them easier to manage compared to the data stored in Container .

Purpose of Docker Volumes : 
Volumes for Persistence: Ensure data remains across container restarts.

Volumes for Development: Enable live reloading of code changes.

Volumes for Configuration: Allow dynamic configuration changes.

Volumes for Isolation: Keep data separate from container lifecycle.

Volumes for Performance: Optimize I/O operations.

Basic Commands : 
 Create Volume : docker volume create my_volume
 Run container with volume : docker run -d --name my_container -v my_volume:/app/data my_image
 Inspect Volume : docker volume inspect my_volume




